claim: Flublok contains 3x the hemagglutinin (HA) antigen content of standard-dose flu vaccines, which has been linked to greater immunogenicity vs standard-dose flu vaccines.
explanation: A multi-row table detailing various quadrivalent influenza vaccines (standard-dose egg-based, cell culture–based, and high-dose egg-based), their presentations, age indications, hemagglutinin (HA) antigen content per dose, administration route, and thimerosal content. Visible entries include standard-dose egg-based vaccines with 15 µg/0.5 mL HA per strain, cell culture–based vaccines with the same HA content, and a high-dose egg-based vaccine with 60 µg/0.7 mL HA per strain for adults ≥65 years. The table does not include any information on Flublok or its antigen content, and thus it does not support the claim about Flublok containing 3× the HA antigen content compared with standard-dose vaccines. does not support the claim Note: Image shows only part of the full vaccine table; Flublok (recombinant vaccine) is not visible in the provided segment.
